    "created_at": "2014-10-01T14:58:11Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-10-01T14:58:11Z",
    "body": "And how would the compiler deduce which references in FFI code are safe and which are not?\n\n``` rust\nstruct Handle<'a> {\n    ptr: &'a *mut JSObject,\n}\n\nimpl<'a> Handle<'a> {\n    unsafe fn get(&self) -> *const *mut JSObject {\n        self.ptr\n    }\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    unsafe { \n        f(handle.get());\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThere is no need to change the FFI code at all.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
